CITY OF DETROIT vs. BOARD OF WATER COMMISSIONERS, No. 15246; 66 N. W., 377; 2 D. L. N., 915.

(Certiorari to Wayne.)

To compel the board to supply water to the Detroit House of Correction free of charge.

The circuit judge granted the writ.

Reversed March 3, 1896, with costs of both courts.
